args:
Though the angels and apostles defeat the new
threat, that also proves to be part of Loki's plan.
With its demise, the last condition for Satan's
revival is met, and he is reborn with the true
mastermind, Origa, as his vessel.
I was supposed to stand...apart...\nTo rule over all...as pope...
Heh heh... AAAAH HA HA HA!
Alas, you've realized just a bit too late.\nWith dear Graht's death, the final\npreparations are complete.
Offered up the 666th sacrifice in a truly\nbreathtaking display of incompetence?\nYeeees! That's EXACTLY what it means!
And now, at long last, it begins!\nSatan's advent is upon us!
Then everything until now has been...
Hold it together! As long as we have\nBasileus, they don't have the vessel!\nThe rite can't be completed!
Really, Nevin? I'm disappointed you\nhaven't seen through the lie I told you\nall the way back in Rozcimea.
Oh yes. It is not I who will become his\nvessel—it is her.
The support is most appreciated, Origa.
Think nothing of it. You two have\nperformed your duties well, and now\nour plans are complete.
Indeed, Satan's resurrection was all\nOriga's idea! Basileus and I have merely\nbeen following her the entire time.
Which means Cardinal Graht was just\na sacrificial lamb led merrily along to\nthe slaughter.
But what could you possibly hope to gain\nby reviving such an evil?
I seek to save this world from\nthe Progenitor.
Origa, I don't understand any of this.\nWhat's going on?!
What could you possibly be chasing?\nIs this really what will make you happy?!
If I do not acquire Satan's power now,\nthe Progenitor will close off all\npossibilities for this world's future.
You couldn't begin to understand the horror\nof seeing all your potential crushed before\nyou—of your will being stripped away.
But I have seen it, and I know there is\nno happiness to be found there. Instead,\nthere is simply...nothing.
That is why I do this. I claim happiness\nfor myself the only way I can!
You don't have to go through this world\nalone, Origa! We talked about this!
It's still not too late. Let me help you!\nLean on your big sister this once, and I\nswear I'll never let go of your hand again!
As I told you, sister, the hour is too late.\nThese hands are sullied now, and their\ntouch would only defile you.
Even so, I will seize happiness for myself\nand make the world know salvation.\nFor this...
Ha ha ha! Wonderful! Truly wonderful!\nThis day is finally here!
Satan's glorious rebirth is upon us!
